OL,6,FA judge-led statutory inquiry, unlike
OL,7,Fa non-statutory inquiry, has legal
OL,8,Fauthority.
OL,10,FStatutory inquiries have the power to
OL,11,Fmake people give evidence and to
OL,12,Fappear as witnesses.
OL,14,FIf you fail to produce asked for
OL,15,Fevidence or appear before a statutory
OL,16,Finquiry, without a reasonable excuse,
OL,17,Fyou will be guilty of a crime.
OL,19,FThe public also, with occasional
OL,20,Frestrictions, can access information
OL,21,Ffrom the inquiry.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/12
